  <Vulnerability Ordinal="1" xmlns="http://www.icasi.org/CVRF/schema/vuln/1.1">
    <Title>Cisco TelePresence TC and TE Software Authentication Bypass Vulnerability</Title>
    <ID SystemName="Cisco Bug ID">CSCub67651</ID>
    <Notes>
      <Note Title="Summary" Type="Summary" Ordinal="1">A vulnerability in the authentication code of Cisco TelePresence TC and TE Software could allow an unauthenticated attacker within the broadcast or collision domains, or with physical access to the system, to bypass authentication and obtain root user access to the affected system.



The
vulnerability is due to the improper implementation of authentication and
authorization controls for internal services. An attacker could exploit this
vulnerability by connecting to the affected service.</Note>
      <Note Title="Cisco Bug IDs" Type="Other" Ordinal="3">CSCub67651</Note>
    </Notes>
